NUMBER 161 
NAME House, right side
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The path to the right of the house is narrow and made of cobblestone. There 
are two windows with sky blue drapes. As you continue on you begin to see
the back yard. You start to notice a familiar smell.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SW 153
EXIT NW 163

ITEM 0 475
ITEM 1 475

IFPREVERB SMELL -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You cant seem to place the smell but it is getting stronger as you move on.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SEARCH -1
  IFVAR SKILL21 > 5
    ECHO PLAYER You notice the second window is unlocked.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH 1
  GMMSG The thief has opened the window on the first floor.
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You slowly begin to open window....
  PLREVENT 2
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER It slowly moves up further....
  PLREVENT 2
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER and further until the opening is large enough for you to go through.
  EQUAL FLAG1 1
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The window is closed.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB OPEN 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The window is locked from the inside.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
    GMMSG The thief has got into the first floor through the window.
    ECHO PLAYER You start to enter the window.
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER Small beads of sweat come into being upon your brow as you.....
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER shift your weight in an effort to make no sound.
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    MOVE 332
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The window is closed.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB OPEN 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The window does not open.
ENDIF
 
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  SHOWROOM 332
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 1
  CLEARVERB
  SHOWROOM 332
ENDIF     
; 
